  { question: "What is a miter angle?", answer: "A miter angle is the angle you cut on the end of a board so that two pieces join cleanly at a corner. For a regular polygon with N sides, each miter angle equals 180 divided by N. A square picture frame uses 45° miters, a hexagon uses 30° miters, and an octagon uses 22.5° miters." },
